title: moved dplyr to Imports and updated min ggplot2 version
body:
Per @briatte in #13, moved `dplyr` to `Imports` since it's used in the pkg itself and not just examples. Also updated the ggplot2 dependent version # and the minimum R requirement # (to match the lowest common denominator of all Imported pkgs). 

Also updated the pkg version & date.

title: Added two DESCRIPTION fields
body:
First: This is an EPIC ggplot2 2.0 plug-in/add-on! 

Second: this is a trivial PR

I updated the pkg `DESCRIPTION` to add GitHub links to both the repo and a place for folks to file bug reports. No worries if you want to use other means but I've found using GitHub for pkg issue tracking to be >>> maintainer email. CRAN won't take a pkg update for a month but you may have enhancements ot tweaks before then (if you accept the PR).

This is going to be _very_ popular pkg :-)
